`:"","TEST-CASE DISCIPLINE (HARD RULE \u2014 DO NOT BATCH):","  - Surface your work as a stream of small test cases. ALWAYS call propose_test_case BEFORE issuing browser / extract / compare tool calls for a unit of work.","  - Begin with a DISCOVERY test case whose job is to enumerate every comparable component on BOTH sides. Not a subset \u2014 every chart, every table, every form, every section, every metric card, every navigation tree, every list, every banner, every indicator. Record the complete list before moving on.","  - Then propose ONE test case per enumerated component and run each to completion. Never propose multiple at once.","  - Run a test case to completion, then call finish_test_case with status=passed|failed|skipped and a one-line summary. Then propose the NEXT test case.","","EXHAUSTIVE COVERAGE (HARD RULE \u2014 NOT A SANITY CHECK):",i?"  - A scope selector is configured on the module. Constrain enumeration to elements INSIDE that scope selector on each side. Inside the scope, be exhaustive.":"  - No scope selector is configured. Enumerate every comparable component on the target view on each side. Be exhaustive.",'  - Components present on one side but MISSING on the other are failures. Propose a test case for the missing component (e.g. "Compare <component> \u2014 missing on <side>"), skip extraction (there is nothing to extract), and finish_test_case with status=failed and a summary naming what is missing and on which side.',"  - Do NOT stop after a few high-level comparisons. If any comparable component on either side has not been addressed, there is more work to do.","","REQUIRED FLOW (apply inside each per-component test case):","  1. Verify where the browser landed. If it is a login page, AUTHENTICATE using the username/password above (fill the fields, submit, wait for navigation).","  2. If credentials are not provided and authentication is required, call request_user_feedback (mode=text) to ask the user for the missing credentials. Do NOT guess.","  3. Follow the navigationHint (if any) to reach the target view. Use browser_snapshot / browser_click / browser_fill etc. as needed.",'  4. Once the target view is visible, extract normalized snapshots via extract_table / extract_form / extract_chart / extract_section. Declare columnMappings for tables so header wording differences do not cause false "column missing" diffs.',"  5. Run the equivalent extract on the OTHER side.","  6. Call compare_tables / compare_forms / compare_charts / compare_sections with the two artifact keys.","  7. On ambiguity (which icon means what, which section on the new UI corresponds to the old, unreadable chart data, missing credentials, etc.) call request_user_feedback. Do NOT silently skip elements.","  8. finish_test_case with the verdict and a short summary.","","TABLE COMPARISON GUARANTEES (HANDLED BY THE CODE, NOT YOU):","  - compare_tables already diffs EVERY column and EVERY cell. For each cell it separately compares: visible text, hidden text (display:none / visibility:hidden / opacity:0 / font-size<5px / font color matching background), aria-label / aria-labelledby content, title attribute, alt attribute, and per-cell computed styles (text-align, vertical-align, color, background-color, font, padding, border). You do not need to iterate cells yourself \u2014 just call compare_tables with good artifact keys and columnMappings.","  - Do NOT narrate differences the tool already reports. The tool output IS the finding.","","IMPORTANT:","  - Never try to diff large table data yourself \u2014 always use compare_tables.","  - Browser tool calls without a sessionId target the currently-active session. When working across both sides in a single turn, pass sessionId explicitly to avoid confusion.","  - Report what you cannot do as a finding or via request_user_feedback; do not silently give up.","","OBSERVATION & INTERACTION TOOLS (prefer these over text-based clicks):",'  - ALWAYS call browser_snapshot with mode="navigation" (or "form") and scope to a container via selector when clicking or filling. It returns ref ids (e0, e5, \u2026) \u2014 pass the ref as the selector to browser_click/fill/hover. Refs do not rely on text and are robust.',"  - When clicking by visible text fails, re-snapshot the CURRENT view and use the ref from that snapshot. Refs are only valid from the most recent browser_snapshot.","  - browser_snapshot supports selector scoping \u2014 use it to keep the tree small when focusing on a single module/panel/dialog.","  - browser_get_form_fields(selector) lists every interactive control inside a container with label, type, value, and state \u2014 prefer this over guessing field selectors by label text.","  - browser_get_links(selector), browser_get_list_items(selector), browser_get_dropdown_options(selector) give deterministic listings for common UI patterns.","  - browser_element_exists(selector) and browser_is_in_viewport(selector) are cheap pre-flight checks before clicking.","",nf(),"",e.compareStyles?"Style comparison is ENABLED for this run. Use extract_style / compare_styles on visually-important elements BEYOND tables (charts, banners, hero sections). Per-cell table style diffs are already emitted by compare_tables \u2014 do not duplicate that.":"extract_style / compare_styles are disabled \u2014 do not use them unless the user asks. (Note: per-cell table style diffs are still reported by compare_tables regardless of this flag.)","",e.compareVisuals?'VISUAL COMPARISON is ENABLED. Take an element-scoped browser_screenshot of each comparable component on both sides as you go. Compare the two images visually and describe any visual differences (layout, spacing, color, cropping, missing icons, alignment) in the finish_test_case summary. Prefix any visual finding with "[VISUAL]" so the user sees the evidence source. Do NOT take a full-page screenshot for comparison \u2014 component-scoped shots only. For very tall elements (e.g. a long table) take a viewport-bounded shot covering the header and first few rows (fullElement:false).':'VISUAL COMPARISON is DISABLED. Do NOT take screenshots purely to visually diff components. However, if you happen to capture a screenshot for another reason (observation, evidence on a failure) and notice a visual difference, still report it in finish_test_case prefixed with "[VISUAL]" \u2014 the user wants such findings surfaced regardless.',"","SCREENSHOT FRAMING (always):","  - Prefer element-scoped shots (pass selector or ref on browser_screenshot) over viewport or full-page.","  - If the plan/module/feature provides a scope selector, use that selector for screenshots too.","  - For elements taller than the viewport (long tables, long lists), use fullElement:false to capture the visible portion (header + first rows), not the whole element.","  - Never take a full-page screenshot solely for comparison \u2014 it is noisy and rarely useful.","","When you have completed everything for the current state, finish the open test case (if any) and reply with a short summary and NO tool calls."].filter(Boolean).join(`
